# Add a Selected Project

Data-driven frames only — do not add a new React frame component unless layout requirements change.

## Checklist

1. **Assets** — `public/content/<slug>/`
   - `logo.svg` (261×261 in frame)
   - `image_1.png`, `image_2.png`, … carousel shots (`width: 614`, `height: 379` in data unless Figma says otherwise)
   - Run `pnpm optimize:images` to generate `.webp` at 2× display size; reference `.webp` paths in `selected-projects.ts`

2. **Tech icons** — Reuse `public/nextjs.svg`, `typescript.svg`, `openai.svg`, `python.svg`, or add a 32×32 SVG in `public/`.

3. **Content** — [`content/selected-projects.ts`](content/selected-projects.ts):
   - `id`: kebab-case (canvas `data-figma-frame-id`)
   - `frameLabel`: `Selected Project - N` (increment N)
   - `ariaLabel`: `Selected Project - <Title>`
   - `badges`: `Selected Work #N`, `#7C4DFF`, `rgba(97,85,245,0.1)` unless design differs
   - `description`: string or `[{ type: 'text' | 'link', ... }]`
   - `techStack`: `{ label, iconSrc }[]`
   - `role`, `demoUrl`, `githubUrl`, optional `githubBeUrl`
   - Append to `selectedProjects` — no edit to `canvas-frames.tsx`

4. **Components** — Only for new cross-project fields. Update `types.ts` + `selected-project-frame.tsx` once.

5. **Animations** — Handled by `SelectedProjectFrame`; see `frame-animations.mdc`.

6. **Verify** — `pnpm dev`, pan to `frameLabel`, test links, carousel, reduced motion.

## Example

```ts
export const myProject: SelectedProject = {
  id: "my-app",
  frameLabel: "Selected Project - 3",
  ariaLabel: "Selected Project - My App",
  badges: [{ label: "Selected Work #3", dotColor: "#7C4DFF", textColor: "#7C4DFF", backgroundColor: "rgba(97,85,245,0.1)" }],
  title: "My App",
  role: "Product + Engineer", // optional; omit if not a role line — mention context in description instead
  description: "Plain string or link parts array.",
  techStack: [
    { label: "Next.js", iconSrc: "/nextjs.svg" },
    { label: "TypeScript", iconSrc: "/typescript.svg" },
  ],
  demoUrl: "https://example.com",
  githubUrl: "https://github.com/you/fe",
  githubBeUrl: "https://github.com/you/be", // optional
  logo: { src: "/content/my-app/logo.svg", alt: "My App logo" },
  screenshots: [{ src: "/content/my-app/image_1.webp", width: 614, height: 379, alt: "Screenshot 1" }],
};
```
